1
00:00:02,202 --> 00:00:04,605
<i>Just another chicken place</i>
<i>in and around Seoul.</i>

2
00:00:05,472 --> 00:00:07,374
<i>The smell of frying oil is strong,</i>

3
00:00:07,441 --> 00:00:09,843
<i>but the sisters' passion is stronger.</i>

4
00:00:13,213 --> 00:00:15,949
<i>It's known as a hangout spot</i>
<i>for various clubs.</i>

5
00:00:18,418 --> 00:00:20,020
What are all these plaques for?

6
00:00:20,087 --> 00:00:22,689
LEE SUN-JA: YOUNGER TWIN
They represent my career.

7
00:00:22,756 --> 00:00:24,191
I was running clubs

8
00:00:24,258 --> 00:00:25,659
before I opened this place.

9
00:00:25,726 --> 00:00:27,694
I ran so many different clubs.

10
00:00:27,828 --> 00:00:29,129
I can't even count them.

11
00:00:29,196 --> 00:00:30,864
Too many to tell.

12
00:00:30,931 --> 00:00:31,765
APPRECIATION PLAQUE

13
00:00:31,832 --> 00:00:34,368
If you look at this one...
Sorry, just a moment.

14
00:00:34,735 --> 00:00:35,903
Gosh, bad timing.

15
00:00:36,103 --> 00:00:37,170
Hello?

16
00:00:37,604 --> 00:00:39,439
Ski!

17
00:00:39,673 --> 00:00:41,408
The great Ski Yoon.

18
00:00:41,508 --> 00:00:44,144
Of course, we should all
get chicken after skiing.

19
00:00:44,211 --> 00:00:46,813
Fried chicken after skiing
is the best, isn't it?

20
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:49,783
<i>- Sun-ja's busy with the clubs as always.</i>
- Okay, then...

21
00:00:49,950 --> 00:00:52,753
<i>Our restaurant is always lively</i>
<i>with club gatherings.</i>

22
00:00:52,819 --> 00:00:54,321
Come on an empty stomach.

23
00:00:55,289 --> 00:00:56,390
LEE SUN-I: OLDER TWIN

24
00:00:56,456 --> 00:00:57,624
Jeez.

25
00:00:59,393 --> 00:01:00,561
Damn it.

26
00:01:02,663 --> 00:01:05,632
What would this restaurant be without me?

27
00:01:05,699 --> 00:01:07,768
I deliver orders, I hand out coupons...

28
00:01:07,834 --> 00:01:10,871
CHICKEN SISTERS

29
00:01:10,938 --> 00:01:11,838
There are too many.

30
00:01:11,905 --> 00:01:13,707
Cops and Robbers, Easy Runners...

31
00:01:13,774 --> 00:01:15,275
- Gosh, it's cold.
- So many.

32
00:01:15,342 --> 00:01:17,044
- I've been running around like crazy.
- So...

33
00:01:17,110 --> 00:01:19,112
- Hey.
- What would you do without me?

34
00:01:19,179 --> 00:01:20,314
Delivery's done.

35
00:01:20,380 --> 00:01:21,915
- Great job.
- Are you the CEO?

36
00:01:21,982 --> 00:01:23,617
Yes, I am the CEO.

37
00:01:23,984 --> 00:01:25,485
See? I don't look like a deliveryperson.

38
00:01:26,253 --> 00:01:27,888
You should say it straight.

39
00:01:27,955 --> 00:01:30,157
Hello, welcome to Chicken Sisters.

40
00:01:30,223 --> 00:01:32,559
I'm the CEO, Sun-ja.

41
00:01:32,626 --> 00:01:34,528
I'm the CEO, not you.

42
00:01:34,595 --> 00:01:36,730
Hello there, I'm the CEO.

43
00:01:36,797 --> 00:01:40,634
I covered 70% of the initial investment.

44
00:01:40,701 --> 00:01:42,069
- What are you talking about?
- Oh, my.

45
00:01:42,135 --> 00:01:43,270
- That's crazy talk.
- Stop that.

46
00:01:43,337 --> 00:01:44,705
- She's younger.
- On TV,

47
00:01:44,771 --> 00:01:46,807
- I'm the CEO.
- none of this would air.

48
00:01:46,873 --> 00:01:50,777
<i>My twin older sisters fight,</i>
<i>but they can't live without each other.</i>

49
00:01:50,844 --> 00:01:52,479
I'm the CEO, yes.

50
00:01:52,546 --> 00:01:54,881
It's not common to have this many sisters.
It must be nice with them around.

51
00:01:55,182 --> 00:01:58,218
Oh, we have more sisters. Seven in total.

52
00:01:58,285 --> 00:02:01,722
Our two older sisters run a tea house.

53
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:03,156
We're the third and fourth.

54
00:02:03,223 --> 00:02:05,058
Us, Sun-ja and Sun-i.

55
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:06,960
As for the fifth and sixth sisters...

56
00:02:07,594 --> 00:02:09,496
I have no idea,
but I'm sure they're doing well somewhere.

57
00:02:09,563 --> 00:02:11,798
And our seventh
and youngest sister is Min.

58
00:02:12,032 --> 00:02:14,568
She runs the restaurant with us.

59
00:02:14,635 --> 00:02:16,403
She's helping out her older sisters.

60
00:02:17,004 --> 00:02:19,706
I'm so sorry.
My phone keeps blowing up today.

61
00:02:19,773 --> 00:02:22,009
- I'm too busy.
- Lift your feet up.

62
00:02:23,043 --> 00:02:24,144
Hello?

63
00:02:24,478 --> 00:02:28,315
Sun-ja, Yi-rang is driving me crazy!

64
00:02:29,016 --> 00:02:29,983
It's my second-oldest sister.

65
00:02:30,050 --> 00:02:32,853
She and the oldest run
a tea house called Dabang Sisters.

66
00:02:32,919 --> 00:02:33,954
Hey, Su-ji.

67
00:02:34,021 --> 00:02:35,989
What's gotten you so riled up?

68
00:02:36,056 --> 00:02:38,191
What did she do this time?

69
00:02:38,258 --> 00:02:40,761
She bought years' worth of <i>ssanghwa</i> tea

70
00:02:40,827 --> 00:02:43,130
without even checking the books.

71
00:02:43,497 --> 00:02:45,899
Gosh, there's never a dull moment
with you two.

72
00:02:45,966 --> 00:02:47,701
You're always bickering.

73
00:02:47,768 --> 00:02:50,737
Same here.
Sun-i is as uncultured as always.

74
00:02:50,804 --> 00:02:51,772
There's never a dull moment here too.

75
00:02:51,838 --> 00:02:53,440
Uncultured? You're uncultured!

76
00:02:53,507 --> 00:02:54,775
- Su-ji, I've got to go.
- What are you talking about?

77
00:02:54,841 --> 00:02:55,942
Sun-i's being silly.

78
00:02:56,009 --> 00:02:57,477
Su-ji, be nice to Yi-rang.

79
00:02:57,544 --> 00:02:58,679
I hung up, you dumb bitch.

80
00:02:58,745 --> 00:03:00,847
Bitch, are you out of your mind?

81
00:03:00,914 --> 00:03:01,882
No, you are.

82
00:03:01,948 --> 00:03:03,183
I'm working my butt off.

83
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:04,718
You never sweep the floor.

84
00:03:04,785 --> 00:03:06,420
I already swept the floor.

85
00:03:06,486 --> 00:03:07,421
That's why it's spotless.

86
00:03:07,487 --> 00:03:10,023
- I'm folding boxes.
- This is why Yi-rang hates you.

87
00:03:10,090 --> 00:03:11,892
- So loud.
- And she's a good person.

88
00:03:11,958 --> 00:03:13,727
- Don't talk to me.
- You...

89
00:03:13,794 --> 00:03:17,064
<i>Their bickering is always</i>
<i>louder than the sound of frying.</i>

90
00:03:18,198 --> 00:03:21,468
CHICKEN SISTERS

91
00:03:22,202 --> 00:03:25,038
EPISODE 1: SANCTUARY FOR CLUBS

92
00:03:25,105 --> 00:03:27,941
<i>Although they always fight,</i>
<i>they're still sisters.</i>

93
00:03:28,575 --> 00:03:30,711
- This is really good.
- Right?

94
00:03:30,777 --> 00:03:32,446
- How does the sauce taste so good?
- It's good, right?

95
00:03:35,382 --> 00:03:38,585
Sun-i, let's save the legs for our guests.

96
00:03:38,652 --> 00:03:40,520
- You can't eat them all.
- Who says?

97
00:03:40,587 --> 00:03:41,688
Think first, Sun-i.

98
00:03:41,755 --> 00:03:43,156
- Welcome.
- Hey, Sun-ja.

99
00:03:43,523 --> 00:03:45,392
- Won-hun!
- The guests...

100
00:03:45,459 --> 00:03:46,793
- Welcome.
- Hello.

101
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:48,261
- It's cold, right?
- Well...

102
00:03:48,328 --> 00:03:49,930
KIM WON-HUN, RUNNING CLUB MEMBER
I have something to tell you.

103
00:03:49,996 --> 00:03:51,465
- Come sit.
- No, it's fine. I...

104
00:03:51,531 --> 00:03:53,633
Take a seat first. Come here.

105
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:57,404
<i>He apparently never runs with the club</i>
<i>but always joins them for a drink.</i>

106
00:03:57,471 --> 00:03:59,940
- Well, I have something to say.
- What is it?

107
00:04:00,006 --> 00:04:02,209
- We've been running for six months.
- Right.

108
00:04:02,275 --> 00:04:03,376
Has it been six months?

109
00:04:03,443 --> 00:04:06,780
I feel like
the crew's structure is crumbling.

110
00:04:06,847 --> 00:04:07,948
- What do you mean?
- That's possible.

111
00:04:08,014 --> 00:04:08,882
Tell me, Won-hun.

112
00:04:08,949 --> 00:04:10,617
I love your proactivity.

113
00:04:10,684 --> 00:04:12,052
- Go on, tell us.
- Good on you.

114
00:04:12,119 --> 00:04:13,186
What's wrong?

115
00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:15,989
You said the average age is
in the twenties.

116
00:04:16,356 --> 00:04:18,792
I've never seen anyone in their twenties.

117
00:04:18,859 --> 00:04:19,926
That's what you want?

118
00:04:19,993 --> 00:04:22,295
- Someone's got to be in shape
- Someone in their twenties...

119
00:04:22,362 --> 00:04:24,097
so that the rest can follow.

120
00:04:24,164 --> 00:04:25,465
Where's the balance?

121
00:04:25,532 --> 00:04:26,967
I'm as fit as someone in their twenties.

122
00:04:27,033 --> 00:04:28,335
I'm as fit as a teenager.

123
00:04:29,669 --> 00:04:32,539
But your physical age is different

124
00:04:32,606 --> 00:04:33,840
from your real age.

125
00:04:33,907 --> 00:04:37,277
Hold on, we're not
that much older than you.

126
00:04:38,011 --> 00:04:39,513
We were born in 1988.

127
00:04:39,980 --> 00:04:41,348
- You're younger.
- And you, 1989.

128
00:04:41,414 --> 00:04:43,550
If that's true, why are you so...

129
00:04:43,617 --> 00:04:45,252
- So what?
- Wait a second.

130
00:04:45,318 --> 00:04:47,087
I've never seen people like you
among people your age.

131
00:04:47,154 --> 00:04:49,256
- What do you mean?
- We're fit like people our age.

132
00:04:53,894 --> 00:04:55,295
- Wait...
- You want a beer?

133
00:04:55,362 --> 00:04:56,363
- No.
- Have one.

134
00:04:56,429 --> 00:04:59,099
I think we're on different paths.

135
00:04:59,166 --> 00:05:01,067
Let me cut to the chase, I...

136
00:05:01,701 --> 00:05:03,203
I want to leave the club.

137
00:05:03,270 --> 00:05:05,405
I looked into a different running club.

138
00:05:05,472 --> 00:05:08,108
Won-hun, no other running club
is going to want you.

139
00:05:08,175 --> 00:05:10,677
He runs like this. Most people look ahead,

140
00:05:10,744 --> 00:05:13,313
but this bastard looks to the side
to find women in leggings.

141
00:05:13,380 --> 00:05:15,882
- He runs like this.
- I have zero interest in women.

142
00:05:15,949 --> 00:05:18,218
I thought you had a neck cast on.

143
00:05:18,418 --> 00:05:20,253
Because you were running like this.

144
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:22,889
- Why are you mocking me?
- His eyes were crossed.

145
00:05:22,956 --> 00:05:25,392
Hey, there you go. Look all you want.

146
00:05:25,458 --> 00:05:27,594
- I have leggings on too.
- Look over here.

147
00:05:27,794 --> 00:05:29,362
Please don't wear them.

148
00:05:29,596 --> 00:05:32,199
- Would you prefer pink?
<i>- Won-hun sure looks irritated.</i>

149
00:05:32,265 --> 00:05:33,667
Please, listen to me.

150
00:05:33,733 --> 00:05:35,936
- Fine, I'm listening.
- I'm quitting as of today.

151
00:05:36,002 --> 00:05:37,137
Whatever.

152
00:05:37,204 --> 00:05:38,205
Leave if you want.

153
00:05:38,939 --> 00:05:40,607
- Sun-i.
- This is not because of you.

154
00:05:40,674 --> 00:05:43,376
You came here to tell us
you're leaving, so do it.

155
00:05:43,777 --> 00:05:45,545
Why are you looking at me that way?

156
00:05:46,379 --> 00:05:48,448
- Just leave, jeez.
- You want one, Sun-i?

157
00:05:48,515 --> 00:05:50,951
It's too hard to run
with just the three of us.

158
00:05:51,017 --> 00:05:52,252
Our paces don't match.

159
00:05:52,319 --> 00:05:53,820
What do you mean?

160
00:05:53,887 --> 00:05:55,789
Have you ever even felt a runner's high?

161
00:05:55,856 --> 00:05:57,023
Of course, you haven't.

162
00:05:57,090 --> 00:05:58,358
What's a runner's high?

163
00:05:58,625 --> 00:06:00,360
It's when you suddenly feel

164
00:06:00,427 --> 00:06:03,330
this kind of cathartic euphoria
after intense running.

165
00:06:03,396 --> 00:06:06,333
Yes, I get that high every time I eat.

166
00:06:09,102 --> 00:06:10,136
No, from running.

167
00:06:10,203 --> 00:06:12,939
- See? This club is wrong for me.
- Having fried chicken

168
00:06:13,006 --> 00:06:14,140
- after running
- Hold on.

169
00:06:14,207 --> 00:06:15,976
- can give you a high.
- Who's that?

170
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:17,878
- A catharsis.
- This picture

171
00:06:17,944 --> 00:06:19,679
doesn't even make sense.

172
00:06:19,746 --> 00:06:22,649
Where are all these women now?

173
00:06:22,716 --> 00:06:24,184
We're right here.

174
00:06:24,251 --> 00:06:26,519
- Right here.
- No, these other women.

175
00:06:26,586 --> 00:06:27,988
- Right here.
- I've never seen them.

176
00:06:28,054 --> 00:06:28,989
- Here.
- Here.

177
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:30,824
Why is it always just us three?

178
00:06:30,891 --> 00:06:32,826
- I have to go.
- Take a seat.

179
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:35,395
- That's our baby sister.
- I'm telling you I want to leave.

180
00:06:35,462 --> 00:06:36,997
Why are you stopping me?

181
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:38,832
All right, you can leave.

182
00:06:38,899 --> 00:06:40,834
But since you're here, have a beer.

183
00:06:40,901 --> 00:06:42,068
Sun-i!

184
00:06:42,335 --> 00:06:44,571
- Sun-i...
- You're Sun-i, you dumbass.

185
00:06:44,638 --> 00:06:46,907
Are you even paying attention?

186
00:06:46,973 --> 00:06:48,308
Wait, hold on.

187
00:06:48,375 --> 00:06:49,876
Sorry, it's her first day
as this character.

188
00:06:49,943 --> 00:06:51,678
She doesn't know all the names yet.

189
00:06:51,745 --> 00:06:53,480
- That was hilarious!
- Come on.

190
00:06:53,546 --> 00:06:55,181
I hate people breaking character.

191
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:56,549
- Come on, sit down.
- Min!

192
00:06:56,616 --> 00:06:58,318
Can you get me a glass of water?

193
00:06:58,652 --> 00:07:00,186
Hey, don't boss her around.

194
00:07:01,321 --> 00:07:02,956
What about you?

195
00:07:08,828 --> 00:07:10,797
You boss her around all the time.

196
00:07:10,864 --> 00:07:13,300
You've been bossing me around
since we were kids.

197
00:07:13,366 --> 00:07:16,169
Our youngest sister.
The only one who resembles me.

198
00:07:16,236 --> 00:07:18,204
- Your neck is stuck facing backward.
- No, it's not.

199
00:07:18,271 --> 00:07:20,674
- Hold on.
- See? I told you he does that.

200
00:07:20,941 --> 00:07:23,009
- That must be heavy.
- Stop eyeing her!

201
00:07:23,076 --> 00:07:25,178
- I'm okay, really!
- Let me.

202
00:07:25,245 --> 00:07:26,846
Jeez, what are you doing?

203
00:07:26,913 --> 00:07:27,914
She can handle it.

204
00:07:27,981 --> 00:07:29,082
How do you know her?

205
00:07:29,149 --> 00:07:30,550
- Our youngest sister.
- Our youngest sister.

206
00:07:30,617 --> 00:07:31,618
Don't we look alike?

207
00:07:31,685 --> 00:07:32,719
A half-sister?

208
00:07:32,786 --> 00:07:34,688
- What do you mean?
- Are you crazy?

209
00:07:34,754 --> 00:07:35,822
We're twins,

210
00:07:35,889 --> 00:07:37,457
and she's our baby sister.

211
00:07:37,524 --> 00:07:39,459
She and I share similar genes.

212
00:07:39,526 --> 00:07:43,730
She's pretty, but she's tough.
You can tell, right?

213
00:07:45,565 --> 00:07:46,733
- What?
- That's enough.

214
00:07:47,834 --> 00:07:49,769
How can your genes be so different?

215
00:07:49,970 --> 00:07:51,738
- Min.
- When I was 20,

216
00:07:51,805 --> 00:07:53,606
- I looked like that.
- Min, get me a glass of water!

217
00:07:53,673 --> 00:07:55,475
- Get it yourself.
- You know

218
00:07:55,542 --> 00:07:58,044
how we have a running club?

219
00:07:58,111 --> 00:07:59,779
You should join us sometime.

220
00:08:00,747 --> 00:08:02,349
<i>Someone's girl-crazy.</i>

221
00:08:02,415 --> 00:08:03,883
- Like, come on.
- Come here.

222
00:08:03,950 --> 00:08:05,418
This is your seat, Won-hun.

223
00:08:05,752 --> 00:08:06,920
Take a seat.

224
00:08:06,987 --> 00:08:07,887
Min.

225
00:08:08,421 --> 00:08:11,057
Okay, so what about your membership fee...

226
00:08:11,191 --> 00:08:12,359
- Won-hun, I'm here.
- Yes.

227
00:08:12,425 --> 00:08:13,727
- Yes.
- I'm talking here.

228
00:08:13,793 --> 00:08:15,562
Don't leave.

229
00:08:15,628 --> 00:08:17,697
I'll wire you the last six months' fee.

230
00:08:17,764 --> 00:08:19,065
- Are you crazy?
- Just go!

231
00:08:19,132 --> 00:08:20,233
That's a lot of money.

232
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:22,035
In a company...

233
00:08:22,102 --> 00:08:23,670
<i>He seems unhappy.</i>

234
00:08:23,737 --> 00:08:25,405
We're losing a source of income.

235
00:08:25,472 --> 00:08:27,607
Sun-ja, Sun-i, I'm really leaving now.

236
00:08:27,674 --> 00:08:29,142
- See you next time.
- Bye.

237
00:08:29,209 --> 00:08:31,311
I hope we meet again in a better place.

238
00:08:31,378 --> 00:08:32,846
Maybe in a different club.

239
00:08:32,912 --> 00:08:34,681
- Okay.
- Thanks for everything.

240
00:08:34,748 --> 00:08:37,951
- Okay.
- I've learned a lot from you.

241
00:08:38,018 --> 00:08:40,887
- About what running really is.
- Right.

242
00:08:41,154 --> 00:08:42,655
I think your passion

243
00:08:42,722 --> 00:08:44,591
helped me grow and improve.

244
00:08:45,091 --> 00:08:46,259
- So long, then.
- Bye.

245
00:08:46,326 --> 00:08:47,627
- Bye.
- Damn it!

246
00:08:49,763 --> 00:08:51,498
- Wait a minute.
- What is it?

247
00:08:51,765 --> 00:08:53,266
- You're hesitant?
- My bus is coming

248
00:08:53,333 --> 00:08:54,601
in three minutes.

249
00:08:54,667 --> 00:08:55,769
- I see.
- Let me wait here.

250
00:08:55,835 --> 00:08:57,137
- Way to drag it out.
- Come on.

251
00:08:57,203 --> 00:08:58,772
You said you're going.

252
00:08:59,005 --> 00:09:00,407
I am, but it's cold outside.

253
00:09:00,473 --> 00:09:01,641
- I'll wait for my bus
- Okay.

254
00:09:01,708 --> 00:09:03,076
- in here.
- Embarrassed?

255
00:09:03,143 --> 00:09:04,244
Don't worry about it.

256
00:09:04,310 --> 00:09:05,512
- Sit down.
- I'm going.

257
00:09:05,578 --> 00:09:06,946
Just sit down already.

258
00:09:07,514 --> 00:09:08,948
I swear, I'm leaving on that bus.

259
00:09:09,015 --> 00:09:10,283
- We get it.
- Okay, we get it.

260
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:13,053
I'm never coming back to this club again!

261
00:09:13,119 --> 00:09:15,021
- All right, whatever you want.
- Yes.

262
00:09:15,088 --> 00:09:17,057
My bus is here. I'm leaving.

263
00:09:17,123 --> 00:09:19,392
- Come on, man.
- Bye.

264
00:09:20,060 --> 00:09:22,462
- Hello.
- Sung-kyoung!

265
00:09:22,529 --> 00:09:24,798
- Hi, everyone.
- Come on in.

266
00:09:24,864 --> 00:09:26,299
LEE SUNG-KYOUNG
THE RUNNING CLUB'S UNICORN

267
00:09:26,599 --> 00:09:27,734
Wait, but...

268
00:09:28,001 --> 00:09:29,602
- Sung-kyoung!
- Hello.

269
00:09:29,669 --> 00:09:30,703
- Hello.
- Come on in.

270
00:09:30,770 --> 00:09:32,872
CHAE JONG-HYEOP, THE RUNNING CLUB'S ACE
Hello.

271
00:09:32,939 --> 00:09:34,307
Come here and take a seat.

272
00:09:34,374 --> 00:09:36,276
- How pretty.
- The bus just left!

273
00:09:36,342 --> 00:09:37,544
It doesn't...

274
00:09:37,677 --> 00:09:39,312
It doesn't wait
when there's no one at the bus stop.

275
00:09:40,013 --> 00:09:42,715
- The bus?
- I had to take that 7612 bus.

276
00:09:45,118 --> 00:09:46,719
When's the next bus coming?

277
00:09:46,786 --> 00:09:49,656
- Right, we're in this picture together.
- Right.

278
00:09:49,722 --> 00:09:51,324
EASY RUNNERS

279
00:09:51,391 --> 00:09:53,193
It's been a while, Sung-kyoung.

280
00:09:53,259 --> 00:09:55,628
- You haven't seen the pictures, right?
- I mean...

281
00:09:55,695 --> 00:09:56,963
- It's been a while, Sung-kyoung.
- Jeez.

282
00:09:57,030 --> 00:09:58,665
- You haven't seen the pictures, right?
- Jong-hyeop.

283
00:09:59,365 --> 00:10:00,300
I took a shower.

284
00:10:00,366 --> 00:10:02,368
It's my first time coming here
since it opened.

285
00:10:02,802 --> 00:10:05,105
- You haven't seen the pictures, right?
- Jeez.

286
00:10:05,338 --> 00:10:08,074
<i>It looks like he fell in love</i>
<i>with Sung-kyoung.</i>

287
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:09,509
Who...

288
00:10:09,576 --> 00:10:11,478
- How are you?
- Yes, hello.

289
00:10:12,912 --> 00:10:14,647
- Where should I sit?
- Wherever you want.

290
00:10:14,714 --> 00:10:17,350
Won-hun, you've never met
Sung-kyoung, have you?

291
00:10:17,417 --> 00:10:19,319
- I didn't even know they were members.
- You're only interested in drinking.

292
00:10:19,385 --> 00:10:21,221
Nobody told me about you.

293
00:10:21,721 --> 00:10:22,856
- I couldn't join often.
- Never?

294
00:10:22,922 --> 00:10:24,491
I couldn't join often.

295
00:10:24,557 --> 00:10:25,792
- I see.
- She doesn't come by often.

296
00:10:25,859 --> 00:10:27,494
This is Sung-kyoung, our member.

297
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:29,963
- Hello.
- You can think of her

298
00:10:30,029 --> 00:10:32,098
as the unicorn of our running club.

299
00:10:32,165 --> 00:10:34,000
I'm the flower of our running club,

300
00:10:34,067 --> 00:10:36,069
- and Sung-kyoung is the unicorn.
- Yes.

301
00:10:36,136 --> 00:10:38,004
I always say this,

302
00:10:38,071 --> 00:10:39,906
- but she's stunning.
- You can go.

303
00:10:40,206 --> 00:10:41,908
This is Jong-hyeop.

304
00:10:41,975 --> 00:10:43,276
You can immediately tell

305
00:10:43,343 --> 00:10:45,678
- that he's our ace.
- And he's so handsome!

306
00:10:45,745 --> 00:10:47,380
- How good are you?
- He's great.

307
00:10:47,447 --> 00:10:48,448
What's your 5K time?

308
00:10:48,515 --> 00:10:49,816
- Tell me.
- On three.

309
00:10:49,883 --> 00:10:50,984
- One, two, three.
- One, two, three.

310
00:10:51,050 --> 00:10:51,918
Thirty-seven.

311
00:10:52,485 --> 00:10:54,087
Oh, you're a slow runner.

312
00:10:55,021 --> 00:10:55,855
Slow and steady.

313
00:10:55,922 --> 00:10:57,457
You're a fucking joke!

314
00:10:57,524 --> 00:10:59,492
You run 5K in 37 minutes?

315
00:10:59,559 --> 00:11:01,127
No need to be so mean about it.

316
00:11:01,861 --> 00:11:03,129
- I mean, come on.
- In 37 minutes?

317
00:11:03,196 --> 00:11:05,865
You're way slower than I am.

318
00:11:05,932 --> 00:11:08,334
I like to enjoy my surroundings
while running.

319
00:11:08,868 --> 00:11:09,903
How about you?

320
00:11:09,969 --> 00:11:13,506
I think it's usually
twenty-something minutes.

321
00:11:13,573 --> 00:11:15,909
- See? Now, that's impressive.
- See?

322
00:11:16,676 --> 00:11:19,913
- I heard there are ten million people
- Really?

323
00:11:19,979 --> 00:11:21,915
- who are currently in running clubs.
- That's right.

324
00:11:21,981 --> 00:11:24,817
You know how they say

325
00:11:24,884 --> 00:11:27,487
that if you wear expensive running shoes,

326
00:11:27,554 --> 00:11:30,557
you'll run better
because they're more comfortable?

327
00:11:30,623 --> 00:11:32,792
Right, some pairs go up to a million won.

328
00:11:32,859 --> 00:11:33,826
I know.

329
00:11:33,893 --> 00:11:36,596
But I can't relate.

330
00:11:36,663 --> 00:11:38,598
I don't take it that seriously.

331
00:11:38,665 --> 00:11:40,200
I just use On running shoes

332
00:11:40,266 --> 00:11:41,568
or Nike ones.

333
00:11:41,634 --> 00:11:43,303
When I really get into something,

334
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:47,240
I focus more on doing that well.

335
00:11:47,307 --> 00:11:48,541
Even when I'm golfing,

336
00:11:48,608 --> 00:11:50,743
people want cute clothes and nice gear,

337
00:11:50,810 --> 00:11:52,845
but I golf in wind pants and a sweatshirt
in winter.

338
00:11:52,912 --> 00:11:55,281
- You're really there to golf.
- Really?

339
00:11:55,348 --> 00:11:57,383
I wear a skirt when the weather's right.

340
00:11:57,450 --> 00:11:59,586
- But never when it's cold.
- I see.

341
00:11:59,652 --> 00:12:00,787
People like to gear up

342
00:12:00,853 --> 00:12:03,156
- and just take pictures.
- That's true.

343
00:12:03,223 --> 00:12:04,390
But you don't care about that?

344
00:12:04,457 --> 00:12:06,559
I have nothing against that, though.

345
00:12:06,626 --> 00:12:08,294
It feels good to run

346
00:12:08,361 --> 00:12:09,929
in cute running clothes.

347
00:12:09,996 --> 00:12:12,165
- Yes.
- Nice clothes change your attitude.

348
00:12:12,232 --> 00:12:13,266
Of course, they do.

349
00:12:13,333 --> 00:12:15,068
I'm sure that motivates people.

350
00:12:15,134 --> 00:12:16,569
Do you run a lot?

351
00:12:16,869 --> 00:12:17,770
I do run, yes.

352
00:12:17,837 --> 00:12:19,072
- I...
- But you have bangs.

353
00:12:19,138 --> 00:12:21,207
They must bother you when you run.

354
00:12:21,274 --> 00:12:23,610
- She runs like this.
- I have these.

355
00:12:24,310 --> 00:12:25,245
My goodness.

356
00:12:26,312 --> 00:12:29,148
- These are headbands that I don't use.
- You little...

357
00:12:29,215 --> 00:12:31,884
I got them secondhand,
but I don't really use them.

358
00:12:31,951 --> 00:12:34,921
They're not my size,
but maybe they're yours.

359
00:12:34,988 --> 00:12:36,889
- You can use them.
- Do you want

360
00:12:36,956 --> 00:12:38,057
- What?
- to share?

361
00:12:38,124 --> 00:12:40,493
- Oh, I have one at home.
- I see.

362
00:12:40,560 --> 00:12:41,494
It's for women.

363
00:12:41,561 --> 00:12:42,695
- I see.
- Thank you.

364
00:12:42,762 --> 00:12:44,664
- Which one would you like?
- Me?

365
00:12:45,198 --> 00:12:47,000
- Thanks.
- Which one would you like?

366
00:12:47,066 --> 00:12:48,534
- Me?
- Let me take a look.

367
00:12:49,102 --> 00:12:50,603
- You're an autumn warm.
- Everything looks good on her.

368
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:51,671
- An autumn warm?
- Then this one?

369
00:12:51,738 --> 00:12:53,239
- I'm actually not.
- No?

370
00:12:53,306 --> 00:12:55,942
<i>Sun-i's face says it all.</i>

371
00:12:56,542 --> 00:12:58,811
- Wait a minute...
- Thank you.

372
00:12:59,279 --> 00:13:00,747
Do you like to go easy?

373
00:13:00,913 --> 00:13:03,816
Well, I only join this club
when I want to go easy.

374
00:13:03,883 --> 00:13:05,285
Should we do a little lap?

375
00:13:05,351 --> 00:13:06,486
No, it's cold outside.

376
00:13:06,552 --> 00:13:08,121
We can do it right here.

377
00:13:08,187 --> 00:13:09,689
I can tell by the way you move.

378
00:13:09,889 --> 00:13:10,990
But...

379
00:13:11,057 --> 00:13:12,492
Okay, the double step.

380
00:13:12,558 --> 00:13:13,993
- Nice.
- Great form.

381
00:13:14,060 --> 00:13:14,894
- I'm a bit like a horse.
- You're good.

382
00:13:14,961 --> 00:13:16,195
- You have a good form.
- I have long strides.

383
00:13:16,663 --> 00:13:18,965
- We should really run together next time.
- Okay.

384
00:13:19,032 --> 00:13:20,233
Do you have a smart watch?

385
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:21,234
- Sorry?
- A watch.

386
00:13:21,301 --> 00:13:25,838
You can use mine. Here.

387
00:13:25,905 --> 00:13:27,473
I don't really use this one.

388
00:13:28,041 --> 00:13:29,575
Use mine, here.

389
00:13:29,642 --> 00:13:31,077
I don't really use this one.

390
00:13:31,911 --> 00:13:33,146
It's never been used.

391
00:13:33,212 --> 00:13:34,514
- It's like you're Doraemon.
- Here.

392
00:13:34,580 --> 00:13:37,483
- Thank you.
- Club members always share.

393
00:13:38,384 --> 00:13:40,453
I feel like it's going to be sweaty.

394
00:13:40,520 --> 00:13:42,155
It's nice to share.

395
00:13:42,588 --> 00:13:43,823
Wait, I almost forgot.

396
00:13:43,890 --> 00:13:44,724
Are you hungry?

397
00:13:44,791 --> 00:13:45,925
- I'll get some food.
- Come on.

398
00:13:45,992 --> 00:13:47,060
Min!

399
00:13:47,126 --> 00:13:49,829
Sun-ja and Sun-i
should be in there like characters.

400
00:13:52,198 --> 00:13:53,566
That's our Min.

401
00:13:53,633 --> 00:13:54,834
Today's special

402
00:13:54,901 --> 00:13:56,436
is evenly cooked chicken

403
00:13:56,502 --> 00:13:58,504
with a crispy exterior.

404
00:13:58,571 --> 00:14:01,274
I call it "Running Chicken."

405
00:14:01,341 --> 00:14:03,409
Let me put it right here.

406
00:14:04,010 --> 00:14:07,180
<i>"Running Chicken," for the Easy Runners!</i>

407
00:14:07,347 --> 00:14:08,448
Look at that.

408
00:14:09,682 --> 00:14:12,485
These are sauces
that are actually exclusive

409
00:14:12,552 --> 00:14:14,187
- to Chicken Sisters.
- That's right.

410
00:14:14,253 --> 00:14:15,121
It's matcha.

411
00:14:15,188 --> 00:14:17,924
Matcha salt, matcha crispy,
and matcha sauce.

412
00:14:18,891 --> 00:14:19,859
That's so cute.

413
00:14:20,093 --> 00:14:22,061
The presentation is excellent.

414
00:14:22,562 --> 00:14:23,796
Come on, let's eat.

415
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:24,964
Full speed...

416
00:14:25,031 --> 00:14:26,199
- In our hearts!
- In our hearts!

417
00:14:26,265 --> 00:14:27,100
Easy...

418
00:14:27,166 --> 00:14:28,000
- In our steps!
- In our steps!

419
00:14:28,067 --> 00:14:29,602
Let's eat!

420
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:32,739
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you.

421
00:14:32,805 --> 00:14:34,340
It's so good.

422
00:14:34,574 --> 00:14:35,708
Matcha salt...

423
00:14:35,775 --> 00:14:38,578
Our baby sister made this herself.

424
00:14:38,644 --> 00:14:40,012
She came up with the idea.

425
00:14:42,482 --> 00:14:44,083
You did great, Min.

426
00:14:44,150 --> 00:14:46,285
- You did well.
- Not only is she pretty just like me...

427
00:14:46,352 --> 00:14:47,553
This tastes very unique.

428
00:14:47,620 --> 00:14:49,589
- Yes, she came up with it.
- Really?

429
00:14:50,256 --> 00:14:52,191
Matcha is trending right now.

430
00:14:52,258 --> 00:14:54,193
That's where she got the idea.

431
00:14:54,260 --> 00:14:55,595
I just had matcha.

432
00:14:55,661 --> 00:14:57,363
- I love it.
- Oh, you like matcha.

433
00:14:57,430 --> 00:14:59,065
I added lemon to it.

434
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:01,134
You added lemon too?

435
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,802
That's why it has a tangy kick.

436
00:15:04,837 --> 00:15:06,305
- It's so unique.
- It's good.

437
00:15:06,706 --> 00:15:08,441
She's an expert on chicken.

438
00:15:08,508 --> 00:15:10,777
She's kind of like a chicken nerd.

439
00:15:10,843 --> 00:15:13,012
<i>My new matcha sauce is a hit!</i>

440
00:15:13,079 --> 00:15:14,747
<i>I'm so proud of myself.</i>

441
00:15:15,148 --> 00:15:16,416
You know what?

442
00:15:16,482 --> 00:15:19,352
There's a series
that I've been wanting to watch.

443
00:15:19,419 --> 00:15:20,386
What is it?

444
00:15:21,387 --> 00:15:24,290
It's a Japanese series. A J-drama.

445
00:15:24,357 --> 00:15:25,825
J-dramas are hot these days.

446
00:15:25,892 --> 00:15:27,460
<i>- Eye Love You.</i>
<i>- Eye Love You.</i>

447
00:15:27,527 --> 00:15:29,529
- That's a good one.
- I heard it's good.

448
00:15:29,595 --> 00:15:31,697
- I see.
<i>- Eye Love You.</i>

449
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:33,633
I heard it's good.

450
00:15:33,699 --> 00:15:34,834
I'm going to watch it.

451
00:15:34,901 --> 00:15:37,670
I heard they took
the key elements of romantic K-dramas

452
00:15:37,737 --> 00:15:40,807
and jam-packed them in the series.

453
00:15:41,407 --> 00:15:42,308
Oh, my.

454
00:15:42,975 --> 00:15:44,577
I'm definitely watching it.

455
00:15:44,844 --> 00:15:46,879
What I heard is

456
00:15:46,946 --> 00:15:50,450
- that they took Japanese fantasies
- Right.

457
00:15:50,516 --> 00:15:53,186
about romance with Korean men

458
00:15:53,252 --> 00:15:56,155
that would've been popular in the '90s

459
00:15:56,222 --> 00:15:59,826
and incorporated them into the male lead.

460
00:15:59,892 --> 00:16:01,227
- Fantasies about men?
- Yes.

461
00:16:01,294 --> 00:16:03,563
I have a lot of fantasies
about romantic men.

462
00:16:03,629 --> 00:16:05,698
It would be so difficult for someone

463
00:16:05,765 --> 00:16:06,866
to pull that off.

464
00:16:06,933 --> 00:16:09,735
- Who's the actor?
- Who pulled that off?

465
00:16:10,770 --> 00:16:13,873
I heard his acting
swept everyone off their feet.

466
00:16:13,940 --> 00:16:17,643
How popular would you say
that actor is in Japan?

467
00:16:19,145 --> 00:16:21,247
- I heard...
- Hey, now.

468
00:16:21,314 --> 00:16:23,549
- Look at that.
- Let's hear it.

469
00:16:23,616 --> 00:16:24,884
Let's hear it.

470
00:16:24,951 --> 00:16:28,187
There hasn't been a TV series

471
00:16:28,621 --> 00:16:30,423
that was number 1
on a streaming service's Top 10 before,

472
00:16:31,023 --> 00:16:32,758
but this one achieved it.

473
00:16:32,825 --> 00:16:34,460
It was number one
on the streaming service in Japan?

474
00:16:34,527 --> 00:16:35,962
Then when you walk around in Japan,

475
00:16:36,028 --> 00:16:38,197
- do people recognize you?
- You're that popular?

476
00:16:38,264 --> 00:16:39,332
"Mr. Hyeop."

477
00:16:39,398 --> 00:16:41,968
Mr. Hyeop? "Mr. Hyeop?"

478
00:16:42,268 --> 00:16:44,437
You're that popular?

479
00:16:44,937 --> 00:16:47,473
I don't know if it'd be like that.

480
00:16:47,540 --> 00:16:50,543
"Mr. Hyeop, please sign here!"

481
00:16:50,610 --> 00:16:52,144
"Mr. Hyeop, sign here."

482
00:16:52,211 --> 00:16:55,114
"Sign, please."

483
00:16:55,748 --> 00:16:58,484
<i>Gosh, there's no stopping them!</i>

484
00:16:59,252 --> 00:17:01,587
- It looks so good!
<i>- Here comes the second special</i>

485
00:17:01,654 --> 00:17:03,322
<i>just for the Easy Runners!</i>

486
00:17:03,389 --> 00:17:04,924
- Goodness.
- You must've been busy.

487
00:17:04,991 --> 00:17:06,692
How great is our Min? Go on, eat.

488
00:17:06,759 --> 00:17:09,829
Sung-kyoung,
working out and running would mean

489
00:17:09,896 --> 00:17:11,631
you generally avoid
this kind of food, right?

490
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:14,967
I don't limit what I eat.

491
00:17:15,034 --> 00:17:17,837
- Come on.
- You probably don't eat much.

492
00:17:18,137 --> 00:17:20,006
People like you eat a tiny bite

493
00:17:20,072 --> 00:17:22,208
and say that you ate a lot.

494
00:17:22,275 --> 00:17:23,576
I don't act like that.

495
00:17:23,643 --> 00:17:26,412
I only say that
after finishing a whole pizza.

496
00:17:26,479 --> 00:17:27,980
- You can finish a whole pizza?
- I don't mean sharing it with others.

497
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:29,048
A large, yes.

498
00:17:29,115 --> 00:17:30,483
- By yourself?
- Yes.

499
00:17:30,750 --> 00:17:31,884
How many burgers?

500
00:17:32,051 --> 00:17:33,519
Burgers? At least three.

501
00:17:33,586 --> 00:17:35,488
When I was younger and still growing.

502
00:17:35,555 --> 00:17:37,089
- And now?
- Now? Two.

503
00:17:37,356 --> 00:17:38,424
- Two burgers?
